results.name: a(n) = round(1/(1-Integral_{x=0..1} f_n(x) dx)), where f_n is the n-th of all functions that are representable as x^x^...^x with m>=1 x's and parentheses inserted in all possible ways.
comment: The ordering of the functions f_n is defined in A215703: f_1, f_2, ... = x, x^x, x^(x^2), x^(x^x), x^(x^3), x^(x^x*x), x^(x^(x^2)), x^(x^(x^x)), x^(x^4), x^(x^x*x^2), ... . Values of new records are in A322008.
